==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æps|-æps]]

===Noun===
'''lapse'''
# a [[temporary]] [[failure]]; a [[slip]].
# a [[decline]] or [[fall]] in [[standard]]s.
# a [[pause]] in [[continuity]].
# an [[interval]] of [[time]] between [[event]]s.
# a [[termination]] of a [[right]] etc, through [[disuse]] or [[neglect]].
# ([[weather]]) A marked [[decrease]] in [[air temperature]] with increasing [[altitude]] because the [[ground]] is warmer than the surrounding air. This [[condition]] usually occurs when skies are clear and between 1100 and 1600 hours, local time. Strong [[convection]] [[currents]] exist during lapse conditions. For [[chemical operations]], the state is defined as [[unstable]]. This condition is normally considered the most [[unfavorable]] for the release of [[chemical agent]]s. See [[lapse rate]].

===Verb===
'''to lapse''' (''transitive'')
# to allow something to lapse
'''to lapse''' (''intransitive'')
# to suffer a lapse

